$\dot{\wv} = - f'(\wv)$

$$ \begin{align*} \Ecal(t) = t (f(\wv) - f^\star) + \frac{1}{2} \| \wv - \wv^\star \|_2^2 \end{align*} $$

$$ \begin{align*} \Ecal'(t) & = f(\wv) - f^\star + t \dot{\wv}^\top f'(\wv) + \dot{\wv}^\top (\wv - \wv^\star) \\ & = - \|f'(\wv)\|_2^2 + f(\wv) - f^\star - f'(\wv)^\top (\wv - \wv^\star) \\ & = - \|f'(\wv)\|_2^2 + f(\wv) + f'(\wv)^\top (\wv^\star - \wv) - f^\star \leq 0 \end{align*} $$

$\Ecal$

$$ \begin{align*} f(\wv) - f^\star \leq \frac{\Ecal(t)}{t} \leq \frac{\Ecal(0)}{t} = \frac{\| \wv_0 - \wv^\star \|_2^2}{2t} = O(1/t) \end{align*} $$

from keras.datasets import imdb
from keras.layers import Dense, Embedding, SimpleRNN
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.preprocessing import sequence

vocabulary = 10000 # 10000
(X_train, y_train), (X_test, y_test) = imdb.load_data(num_words=vocabulary)

#  keyid value +3012
id_to_word = {id_ + 3: word for word, id_ in imdb.get_word_index().items()}

# 0"<pad>" 1"<sos>" 2"<unk>"
for id_, token in enumerate(("<pad>", "<sos>", "<unk>")):
    id_to_word[id_] = token

# 510id
for i in range(5):
    print(X_train[i][:10])
    print(" ".join([id_to_word[id_] for id_ in X_train[i][:10]]))

model = Sequential()
model.add(Embedding(vocabulary, 32))

model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics='acc')
model.summary()
